message.content:
cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.LO, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with finite automata and context-free grammars.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the computational complexity of representing sub- and superword closures of CFGs.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper analyzes the complexity of constructing NFAs for sub- and superword closures of CFGs.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) may be relevant as the paper deals with the representation of languages and the inequivalence problem for NFAs.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) may be relevant as the paper presents an approximation method to attack inequivalence problems for CFGs.
